  <section class="hero">
    <h1><%= title %></h1>
    <p>
      Service projects can support communities in many different ways. 
      Our salsa growing kit project connects to environmental, educational, 
      community service, and health and wellness goals.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="category-grid">
    <article class="category-card">
      <h2>Environmental</h2>
      <p>
        Encourages growing food locally and using simple or recycled containers.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="category-card">
      <h2>Educational</h2>
      <p>
        Teaches people how to grow basic ingredients like tomatoes, peppers, and cilantro.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="category-card">
      <h2>Community Service</h2>
      <p>
        Provides information about recycling to grow plants, growing the plants, and preserving focused on salsa.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="category-card">
      <h2>Health and Wellness</h2>
      <p>
        Promotes access to fresh ingredients and encourages healthier eating habits.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</main>

